=======================================
LATEST VERSION 2.0.0 as PUBPAK for .NET
=======================================

o NAME REBRAND: From "Publish-AppImage" to Pubpak for .NET.
o LICENSE CHANGE: From MIT to GPL-3.0-or-later

o New FLATPAK package output.
o Added "-p, --property" option to command line, allowing properties to be passed to dotnet publish.
o Added "-x, --app-version" option to command line.
o Added "-a, --arch" option to command line.
o Added PKG_TEMP_DIR config option.
o Removed PKG_APPIMAGE_SUFFIX config option which is no longer supported.
o The APP_XML_SRC option renamed to APP_METADATA
o The PKG_APPIMAGE_ARGS option renamed to APPIMAGE_ARGS
o Fixed possible bug with fully qualified output path.
o Demo project updated to .NET 7.
o Other changes, tweaks and updates mainly around support for Flatpak.
o Updated README documentation and associated media.

Note, "Pubpak 2.0 for .NET" is backward compatible with conf files written for "Publish-AppImage".


=======================================
PREVIOUS VERSIONS
=======================================

* * *
Information below this refers to legacy
app called  "Publish-AppImage for .NET".
See: https://github.com/kuiperzone/Publish-AppImage
* * *

VERSION 1.3.1
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Removed redundant echo statements.


VERSION 1.3.0
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Added "launchable" and "provides" to template appdata.xml file. This should avoid pedantic warnings
performed by appimagetool when validating APP_XML_SRC metadata (*).
o Added "--output" option to explicitly specify the final output filename part.
o Demo project updated to .NET 6.
o Minor changes to documentation.

(*) See for info: https://github.com/AppImage/AppImageKit/issues/603


VERSION 1.2.0
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Versioning of project output changed! Removed version (-x) arg from command line. Instead, specify APP_VERSION in the .conf file.
o Added dummy "post-publish.sh" file for test purposes only.
o Updates to readme file and conf file


VERSION 1.1.2
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Updated HelloWorld appdata.xml to avoid warnings.
o Fixed typos in readme
o Added gitignore


VERSION 1.1.1
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Fixed typo.


VERSION 1.1.0
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET

o Exports new APPDIR_ROOT variable.
o Now checks for target binary after POST_PUBLISH (instead of before) in case this command actually creates it.
o Does not create/overwrite AppRun if POST_PUBLISH creates it.


VERSION 1.0.0
Legacy Publish-AppImage for .NET
First release. Tested against .NET SDK 5.0.